l_shapes.py</code> now covers the residual encoder policy, aligned config declarations, norm/activation/bias policy, state-dict prefix shape compatibility, and the accepted SP-A.P1 unused self-attention parameters. The requested verification command passes with all five tests green.</p>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Commands Run</h2>\n    <table>\n      <thead>\n        <tr><th>Command</th><th>Important output</th></tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>git status --short</code></td>\n          <td>Confirmed the worker changed model, train, tests, and added <code>phase1_voxtell_aligned.yaml</code>. The worktree already also contained report/workflow file changes, including <code>workflow_manifest.yaml</code>; this review did not modify those protected files.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>git diff -- Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py Body-Tell/train.py Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py Body-Tell/configs/phase1_voxtell_aligned.yaml</code></td>\n          <td>Reviewed the residual encoder builder, config plumbing in <code>train.py</code>, and updated shape tests.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>conda run -n voxtell python -m pytest Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py</code></td>\n          <td>\n            <pre>collected 5 items\n\nBody-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py .....                               [100%]\n\n============================== 5 passed in 15.54s ==============================</pre>\n          </td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>PYTHONPATH=Body-Tell conda run -n voxtell python -c \"...\"</code></td>\n          <td>\n            <pre>type= ResidualEncoder\noutput_channels= (32, 64, 128, 256, 320, 320)\nstrides= ((1, 1, 1), (2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 2), (2, 2, 2))\nn_blocks_per_stage= (1, 3, 4, 6, 6, 6)\nstage_count= 6\nstage_block_lengths= [1, 3, 4, 6, 6